About this item

  • QUICK & ACCURATE: Built with the highest quality materials, Airmoto is a portable tire inflator for car, trucks, SUVs, motorcycles, and bicycles. Quickly inflate your vehicle's tires in just minutes with precision accuracy up to 120 PSI. Small and compact car air pump that fits in your glove box or trunk.
  • AUTO SHUT OFF: Use the “+” and “-” control buttons on the Airmoto to easily select your desired pressure, simply connect the air hose to your car and press the middle “Start” button on the electric air pump. Once the correct pressure has been reached the Airmoto will automatically shut off. The cordless car tire pump makes it easy to reach all tires without a hassle.
  • MAIN HIGHLIGHTS: Easily change between PSI, kPa, BAR, and KG/CM pressure units with a push of a button; Easy to read large LCD; Digital Tire Pressure Gauge; Built-in LED flashlight for low light conditions; Deflate button for decreasing pressure; Air Hose stores inside; Powerful 2000 mAh rechargeable battery with fast recharging; Rated to 120 PSI.
  • INFLATES ANYTHING: Includes 3 attachments and air hose. Use the Schrader valve on cars, SUVs, motorcycles, and bicycles. Use the Presta valve for a bike tire pump. Needle adapter for sports equipment like basketballs. General adapter for cushions, air pillows and similar. NOTE: Airmoto is not designed for large volume uses like air mattresses, paddle boards or heavy load tires that require a small air compressor.
  • INVEST IN PEACE OF MIND: Perfect gifts for women and gifts for men. Conveniently store this portable air compressor for car tires in your glove box or garage, ready for use whenever needed. The package comprises 1* Airmoto Car Tire Inflator, 1* Air Hose with Schrader attached, 1x General Nozzle Cone, 1* Needle Adapter, 1* Presta Adapter, 1* USB-C Charging Cable, 1* Carrying Case and 1* User Manual. For any questions or concerns, please feel free to contact us.

      How can I use my Airmoto?

      Your Airmoto can inflate most automobile tires, motorcycles, go-karts, bicycles, basketballs, ATVs, UTVs, golf carts, and more. It's rated up to 120 PSI and comes with all the attachments you need for proper inflation.

      How long does it take to inflate a tire?

      Bicycles and road bikes: 2-4 minutes

      Motorcycles: 4-8 minutes

      Average car tire: 4-10 minutes (low pressure), 10-15 minutes (flat or nearly flat)

      Basketballs (and similar items): 1-3 minutes

      How long does it take to charge and how long does it hold a charge?

      The Airmoto takes between 2-3 hours to fully charge and can hold that charge for up to 40 minutes of continuous use. For best charging results, we recommend adding the Airmoto PowerKit to your order.

      What accessories does the Airmoto come with?

      The package comprises 1x Airmoto Car Tire Inflator, 1x Air Hose with Schrader attached, 1x General Nozzle Cone, 1x Needle Adapter, 1x Presta Adapter, 1x USB-C Charging Cable, 1x Carrying Pouch and 1x User Manual

      What is the size and weight of the Airmoto?

      Airmoto is a compact and lightweight device, made for everyone's ease of use. It measures 6 x 2.5 x 1.5 inches weighs 1.2 pounds.

          C. Gray
          5.0 out of 5 stars Wow!!!
          Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
          Size: 1-PackVerified Purchase
          I have "run flat" tires, meaning if a tire is punctured and looses air, you can still drive on the tire for about 50 miles. The novelty is no repairs, calling AAA, etc. However, you have to buy a new tire. One of my tires has a small leak that is problematic during cold weather. (It doesn't leak in the summer and the tread is still very good). Last winter, I went to a gas station about 15 times to top off one tire and balance the weight on all four. I saw this gadget on a YouTube commercial, took notice, and then did my research on Amazon.

          Straight out the box, it took one hour to charge the battery. It hooks up very easily to my computer. I watched all the instructional videos on this site, so I was able to skip the instructions. This baby is very simple to operate. I should point out, after I fully charged the battery, it lost some power overnight. It took six minutes to fill my tire from 26.5PSI to 34PSI. During that time, the battery quickly zapped. (You measure the strength of the charge based on a flashing yellow LED that will change to flashing green, and once it's steady green, it's fully charged). After I used my device for the six minutes that did the trick, it took another 45 minutes to fully charge the battery on my computer.

          PROS: Very compact. Very easy to use. It will make your life easier avoiding gas stations and all the headaches that come with other motorists and scrambling to supply air to your tires in less than two minutes. The sound of the device while pumping is not that bad.

          CONS: You'll have to fully charge the battery before pumping air. I'm sure it connects fine to the port inside my car, but the charging system in a vehicle as opposed to a computer can tend to take more time. It took me six minutes to pump about six pounds - so, I'm guessing one minute for each PSI. If you're pumping more than one tire and require, say a total of 10 PSI's, you're going to have to recharge the battery in order to accomplish such as task.

          Overall, for the price, simplicity, and effectiveness, this is a 5/5 for my needs.

          5.0 out of 5 stars Small but mighty!
          Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
          Size: 1-PackVerified Purchase
          Planning my first long distances motorcycle ride from Mass to NC/TN (Dragons Tail) this summer. Thought it would be a good idea to bring a portable air compressor JUST in case. What caught my eye was this device because of its compact size. Seemed too good to be true. Reviews were mostly amazing compared to other similar products, so I pulled the trigger on this Airmoto Tire Inflator Portable Air Compressor. It came in yesterday and used it on 6 tires today and worked amazing. Operating the buttons is pretty straight forward. Set the PSI you want the tire at, attach the device to the tire, quickly press the power button to activate the air compressor, and you can just walk away and it will shut off once it reaches the PSI you set it too. For example, took MAYBE 2 minutes for each tire, if that, to go from 30 PSI to 35 PSI. This might actually be my "go to" device to inflate all my tires (and soccer balls) from here on out and not mess with my air compressor in my garage which can be cumbersome and the gauge isn't always that accurate...

          UPDATE: A couple of things to note: 1) Not very efficient on larger tires. My truck has 35 inch tires and it took almost one whole charge to add 5 PSI to one tire. Which is fine, I guess, on a pinch, but just something to keep in mind. 2) The bottom of the pump enclosure came loose after just 10 uses and doesn't clip back in securely any more. Pump still works fine though and doesn't impact its performance.

          The Airmoto also works well in non-prime weather conditions. For the trip mentioned above, the temperature in which the Airmoto was performing: Prior to trip: 38F (not bad), First use: 18F (cold!!), second use: 24F (a bit nippy) -- the cold did not affect performance, fill times or accuracy (I have sensors on all my tires that matched the pressure of the Airmoto after filling), she just went right to business filling the tires.

          I have used the Airmoto several times (5+) since the original trip for which it was purchased, and have experienced efficient, powerful and timely operation. She is a little beast!!
